III 18 aspernas = Asprenas 76 ipso = Piso IV 45 examinaretur = exanimaretur VI 15 clavisio = Calvisio. C. IV 8, 27) Tantalus (Eur. Orest. 9 Hor. C. I 28, 7 conviva deorum). Nestor says Of Athene (γ 420) “H μοι ἐναργὴς ἦλθε θεοῦ ἐς δαῖτα θάλειαν, and so the gods, according to Alcinous (η 201 ff), were wont to feast with the Phaeacians. In the Golden Age, in fact, the gods were thought to associate with mortals on terms of equality. See Hes. fr. 218 Mk.
